com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class ListSiperianObjectsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.ListSiperianObjectsRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ListSiperianObjectsRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    Returns metadata of Siperian Hub objects.

    This request is used to obtain basic metadata for a list of Siperian objects that have been configured as a secure resource accessible by the user (see SiperianRequest.setUsername(String)). The metadata contains basic information such as SiperianObjectUID, display name, and description. To obtain the complete metadata, use DescribeSiperianObjectRequest.

    The request, by default, is restricted to return only the objects that are configured as a secure resource and enabled for the user (see setUserResourcesOnly(boolean)). The request can be further restricted to objects that have a specific secure resource privilege (see PrivilegeType) enabled for the user. The metadata for all objects, regardless of the security settings, can be obtained by calling setUserResourcesOnly(false).

    The request can also be restricted to return only objects of a specific type by calling setObjectType(SiperianObjectType). See SiperianObjectType for a list of valid object types.

    Usage Example:

    The following example shows how to request the metadata of the columns for base object "C_PARTY":

    ListSiperianObjectsRequest request = new ListSiperianObjectsRequest();
    request.setObjectType(SiperianObjectType.COLUMN);
    request.setParentUid(SiperianObjectType.PACKAGE.makeUid("C_PARTY"));
    request.setUserResourcesOnly(false); //ignores security access configuration of object
    ListSiperianObjectsResponse response = (ListSiperianObjectsResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    When retrieving a list of users, the parentUid can be optionally set to a specific Role UID to restrict the list to users belonging to that role. To retrieve a list of admin users, the role can be set to ROLE.REQUEST_ADMIN_USERS_ONLY using request.setParentUid(SiperianObjectType.ROLE.makeUid("REQUEST_ADMIN_USERS_ONLY"));.

    Usage Example:

    The following example shows how to request the metadata of users belonging to the role "Manager":

    ListSiperianObjectsRequest request = new ListSiperianObjectsRequest();
    request.setObjectType(SiperianObjectType.USER);
    request.setParentUid(SiperianObjectType.ROLE.makeUid("Manager"));
    request.setUserResourcesOnly(false); //ignores security access configuration of object
    ListSiperianObjectsResponse response = (ListSiperianObjectsResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    DescribeSiperianObjectRequest, Serialized Form

    API Pair: ListSiperianObjectsResponse

    API Group: Metadata
